(50, 1, '2015-11-22 03:54:06', '2015-11-22 03:54:06', 'According to the study conducted by Arts University, Bournemouth, a third of people give up on their dream careers because they did not think they had the right skills. A mentor would be someone who managed to break into those careers or mastered an art and is therefore equipped to advise others on how to follow in their footsteps. As humans, we respond strongly to our fellow humans, and  creating the connection between mentor and mentee will result in real relationships that spark real change. Many historical advances arose out of joint efforts between people. The goal of this site is to empower people to follow their dreams by ensuring everyone has at least one other person they can turn to for encouragement and advice.\r\n\r\nDreamEX is aÂ website that features comprehensive guides for investigating routes to any career or hobby. AÂ trove of information would be made accessible to dreamers for every conceivable dream at varying levels of commitment from a free time hobby to a part-time gig to a full-time career path in the form of question and answer threads on a discussion board. The discussion board is divided into general sections and specialized subsections, becoming a platform for communication between dreamers and their mentors. We also supply links to financial resources, and single page at-a-glance summaries that detail the feasibility of a dream in particular contexts (location, skill set, budget range, etc).', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2015-12-06 04:43:53', '2015-12-06 04:43:53', '', 0, 'http://dreamplanner.campuslifeohs.com/?page_id=50', 0, 'page', '', 0),
